00:30:10.270 --> 00:30:11.645
&gt;&gt;male speaker 2: They are merely an abstraction.

00:30:11.645 --> 00:30:14.820
&gt;&gt;Allen: They might be a useful abstraction,
and you can

00:30:14.820 --> 00:30:16.090
certainly take that view.

00:30:16.090 --> 00:30:20.460
That would be an instrumentalist
interpretation of a theory involving electrons.

00:30:20.460 --> 00:30:25.170
Now, here's a trivial thing that you can do
with that theory,

00:30:25.170 --> 00:30:29.880
electrons, for historical reasons,
have negative charge.

00:30:29.880 --> 00:30:33.750
You could imagine a whole new
physics of the world where you just flip the

00:30:33.750 --> 00:30:35.400
science
of everything.

00:30:35.400 --> 00:30:36.440
Okay?

00:30:36.440 --> 00:30:39.630
That new physics would be just
as good as the old physics, except that electrons,

00:30:39.630 --> 00:30:40.780
in some sense would be different.

00:30:40.780 --> 00:30:42.880
They would have positive charge.

00:30:42.880 --> 00:30:47.840
And it's clear that you haven't done any work
by doing that transition,

00:30:47.840 --> 00:30:50.840
