00:31:59.380 --> 00:32:01.940
If there's a new kind of science going on
here,

00:32:01.940 --> 00:32:04.630
one could imagine there'd be a new kind of
engineering

00:32:04.630 --> 00:32:05.630
that goes with it.

00:32:05.630 --> 00:32:07.110
And I think there is.

00:32:07.110 --> 00:32:09.940
These, again, are some of the axes where I
think

00:32:09.940 --> 00:32:11.820
we're shifting over time.

00:32:11.820 --> 00:32:16.860
Away from engineered systems
that tended to be centralized toward decentralized

00:32:16.860 --> 00:32:17.910
systems.

00:32:17.910 --> 00:32:21.650
Isolation, interaction what I mean by that
is, that in a lot

00:32:21.650 --> 00:32:24.990
of engineering design, if you want to build
something complex,

00:32:24.990 --> 00:32:27.950
that involves many subsystems, you want to
be able

00:32:27.950 --> 00:32:33.700
to design each subsystem in isolation
without having to worry about all the others

00:32:33.700 --> 00:32:35.490
at the same time.

00:32:35.490 --> 00:32:38.430
In the context of, software, this is often
described in terms

00:32:38.430 --> 00:32:43.610
of abstraction and encapsulation, but it's
a fundamental idea through all of engineering,

00:32:43.610 --> 00:32:48.320
that if every component of your system depends
on every other component, you very quickly

00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:50.330
won't
be able to design anything.

00:32:50.330 --> 00:32:53.440
It will collapse
under the weight of its own complexity.

00:32:53.440 --> 00:33:00.570
But that's increasingly, I won't say not true,
I'll say less true that we now have more

00:33:00.570 --> 00:33:06.910
tools for dealing with complexity, and that
allows us to relax a little bit the requirement

00:33:06.910 --> 00:33:09.559
that everything be very carefully isolated.

00:33:09.559 --> 00:33:13.870
We can design things that have more interacting
components now, and still be able to manage

00:33:13.870 --> 00:33:15.460
that.

00:33:15.460 --> 00:33:22.100
One of the ways of managing that is to replace
classical analysis with computation.

00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:24.320
You can design
more complicated things if you throw

00:33:24.320 --> 00:33:28.410
more computational power at it.

