00:34:34.210 --> 00:34:38.220
One more piece of this, so I'm speculating
on a new kind of science, a new kind of modeling,

00:34:38.220 --> 00:34:40.679
a new kind of engineering, and here's a new
kind

00:34:40.679 --> 00:34:42.179
of thinking.

00:34:42.179 --> 00:34:47.540
Which is, I think, our fascination with
Aristotelian logic will gradually fade, and

00:34:47.540 --> 00:34:52.460
be
replaced by some kind of multi-valued logic.

00:34:52.460 --> 00:34:56.720
Being kind of a Bayesian myself, I'm
biased toward Bayesianism as my favorite

00:34:56.720 --> 00:34:59.250
multi-valued logic.

00:34:59.250 --> 00:35:03.150
But that inevitably
takes you on the road from imagining that

00:35:03.150 --> 00:35:07.840
your scientific theories are objective,
or that your beliefs about the world are objective,

00:35:07.840 --> 00:35:14.510
toward acknowledging that they're subjective,
and if they are, then what?

00:35:14.510 --> 00:35:19.830
Subjectivity seems like a dangerous slope
toward pure relativism, you know,

00:35:19.830 --> 00:35:22.520
what's true is true for me, what's true for
you

00:35:22.520 --> 00:35:25.760
is true for you, and we can't talk to each
other.

00:35:25.760 --> 00:35:31.670
That, doesn't seem to be the case, so it raises
the question can we have subjectivity without

00:35:31.670 --> 00:35:33.050
complete collapse?

00:35:33.050 --> 00:35:36.080
A couple of other shifts that I think are
going on,

00:35:36.080 --> 00:35:38.920
away from thinking of scientific theories
in terms

00:35:38.920 --> 00:35:44.310
of Universal Physical Laws, more toward theories
and models.

00:35:44.310 --> 00:35:50.130
I would argue that there's no meaningful difference
between a theory and a model, that when you

00:35:50.130 --> 00:35:52.550
tell me that you're,
that you have a theory, what you're really

00:35:52.550 --> 00:35:57.450
doing
is recommending a model to me.

00:35:57.450 --> 00:36:00.690
And the language that
we would use for choosing one of those models

00:36:00.690 --> 00:36:04.920
again goes back to subjectivity and theory
choice.

00:36:04.920 --> 00:36:07.600
The discussion that Kuhn brings up.

00:36:07.600 --> 00:36:11.619
And the last is away from determinism and
into indeterminism.

